			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hope I don't spoil it for anyone.
<br />

<br />
His primary premise is that climate is worth studying but has not yet been studied empirically.  That global warming is scientificly unfounded with strong evidence showing that it is untrue. In the conclusion he asserts the worst mistake we could make is deluding ourselves into thinking we are omnipotent and capable of predicting or affecting climate on a large scale.  He warns that the same language and hoodoo science was used to justify eugenics in nazi germany, the US (especially California) and the entire western world. He also says in the conclusion that we need to be very careful about politicising research.
<br />

<br />
PLOT RUINING FOLLOWS:
<br />
It was interesting that his book had environmentalists causing a giant sea wave and the recent disaster in Burma etc.  He points out that disasters happen and people use those nature driven events to cull people implanting a belief that they could prevent these things and that it is "their fault" for not acting sooner.<br />_________________<br /><DIV align="CENTER">
