			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The main danger is when science becomes politicized.  This isn't political campaign fodder...it's either a danger or it isn't.  If it isn't, there are plenty of other issues to campaign about.  If it is a danger, it requires solid bipartisan support to deal with it...as united a front we would have if we were invaded by a foreign power.
<br />

<br />
The stakes are high.  <span style="font-style: italic">If</span> human activities are changing the climate, we need to take appropriate measures.  Conversely, if the planet is <span style="font-style: italic">naturally</span> heading toward another ice age (or whatever), it'd be nice to determine if there's anything we can do to prevent it.  Who knows, what we learn today may help us to terraform Mars in the distant future.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
